<section class="hero">
  <h1>The historical record of US democratic norms<br /><i>kept in public.</i></h1>
  <p>
    The Standing documents events involving authoritarianism, anti-democratic
    behavior, and corruption in US governance, applied to all actors regardless of
    party. No anti-democratic action is too small to record: a precinct-level
    incident is filed with the same care as a national one. Every entry is anchored
    to a primary source — a court filing, an agency record, a citizen-captured
    recording — or to two independent investigative outlets. See our
    <a href="/standards/">editorial standards</a>.
  </p>
</section>

{% include "partials/subscribe.njk" %}

<section class="latest">
  <h2>Latest</h2>
  {% if collections.feedEntries.length %}
    {% for entry in collections.feedEntries | head(20) %}
      {% include "partials/entry-card.njk" %}
    {% endfor %}
  {% else %}
    <p><em>No entries yet. The first issue is in preparation.</em></p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section class="explore">
  <h2>Explore by ideal</h2>
  <ul class="ideal-grid">
    {% for ideal in taxonomy.ideals %}
      <li>
        <a href="/ideals/{{ ideal.slug }}/">
          <strong>{{ ideal.title }}</strong>
          <span>{{ ideal.short_description }}</span>
        </a>
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>
